      <hedline>
        <hl1>CHINESE BOND ASSURANCE</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Craig S. Smith</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Smith, Craig S</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Prime Min Zhu Rongji of China says in Tokyo that he will urge Hainan International Trust and Investment Corp to repay Japanese bondholders; Chinese company defaulted on $130 million yen-denominated bond shortly before Zhu traveled to Japan; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Prime Minister Zhu Rongji of China said in Tokyo that he would urge the Hainan International Trust and Investment Corporation to repay Japanese bondholders. The Chinese company defaulted on a $130 million yen-denominated bond last week shortly before Mr. Zhu traveled to Japan. The default has rattled Japanese confidence in the creditworthiness of Chinese state-owned companies.</p>
        <p>Craig S. Smith</p>
      </block>
